description:
**Join Nobula:** Pioneering the Future of Glass 3D Printing

Who are we?

Nobula is an innovative additive manufacturing startup revolutionizing glass applications through our proprietary Direct Glass Laser Deposition (DGLD) technique. Our cutting-edge technology features a laser-based glass 3D printer that uses thin glass filaments as feedstock. With a strong focus on sustainability, our vision is to expand the potential applications of glass 3D printing.

Why is this interesting?

Traditionally, glass fabrication has been expensive, time-consuming, and primarily suited for standardized mass production. However, there is a growing demand for customizable, fast, affordable, and sustainable glass production across various sectors, from life sciences to optics and photonics. Our goal is to enable glass foundries to be placed anywhere, from office desks and labs to production factories.

What have we accomplished?

We have successfully launched pilot projects with both top-tier industial and academical partners. Currently, we are engaged in over 20 active projects. We have also raised more than 55 million SEK in investments from prestigious organizations, including the European Innovation Council (EIC), VCs, business angels, KTH Holding, and the Sting incubator. Our team of 7 operates from an office and lab in central Stockholm, and we are now entering the next phase of scaling.

About the job

We are looking for a brave software developer with skills and experience in machine learning and computer vision to join our team. The role is interdisciplinary, blending programming with hardware and firmware development. Your responsibilities will include:

Supporting project development and communicating effectively both internally and externally;

Developing a system for in-line defect identification and correction for glass 3D printing based on DGLD technology;

Improving existing 3D printing software solutions;

Testing your solutions in real-time processes and implementing them into the device.



You will be part of a driven team of motivated and talented engineers, researchers, and scientists. As we are in a phase of rapid growth, it's the perfect time to join us and dare to dream big.

What we offer

Close collaboration with the founding team in central Stockholm;

An opportunity to shape your own work as an early member of a well-funded startup;

Flexible working schedule;

Equity options for early team members, depending on the role;

Access to a state-of-the-art AM lab in central Stockholm;

A competitive salary.



Required qualifications

Advanced skill in machine learning, computer vision and mechatronics;

Programming skill in C/C++/Python, experience in Linux/Makefile/Git;

At least 1 year of experience in industrial software development;

GitHub administration;

Excellent execution, results-oriented;

Excellent English skills, written and spoken;

Eligibility to work within the EU.



Skills that will make you stand out

Advanced degree in computer science or software development or equivalent;

Experience with computer vision and machine learning;

Have contributed to open-source machine learning projects and or computer vision;

CAD;

Hardware and PCB development;

Embedded MCU programming;

3D printing;

3D scanning;

Algorithm engineering;

High level AI user;

Able to produce high quality code and validation documentation.



Please make your application in English.

Neither CV nor CL are required.

Your LinkedIn profile is sufficient for us to review your application. The profile should have recommendations, certificates, endorsed skills and verified experience.

**What does a Business Developer do?**
* You understand the requirements and needs of our prospects and introduce them to the BrightAnalytics narrative;
* You map out business opportunities through targeted segmentation;
* You expand the number of incoming leads for our Account Executives by setting up targeted sales actions (outbound sales activities, social selling, trade shows, seminars);
* You are always looking for new and creative ways of increasing our name awareness;
* This position is the ideal springboard to a successful B2B sales career!


**Who are you?**
 As part of our European expansion, we are looking for motivated colleagues to join our Stockholm office.




* You hold a master’s degree, preferably in an economic area. Prior work experience is not a must;
* Fluency in Danish is essential due to the platform’s complexity, and fluency in English is a must in our international environment;
* You derive energy from your communication with potential customers and from the discovery and development of business opportunities;
* You have the motivation and self-reliance required to fulfill this pivotal role;
* You are open to learning new things every day;
* As part of the team you are not afraid to go the extra mile;
* You feel in your element in a rapidly evolving environment;
* You have a passion for business, finance and new technologies.


**What can you expect from us?**
* You will be part of a driven, dynamic and enthusiastic team in a varied job;
* Weekly internal training sessions and on-the-job coaching will teach you unique skills that will serve you well throughout your career;
* We are a financially healthy scale-up with international growth ambitions;
* We have an open business culture with room for personal initiative;
* A competitive salary & motivating bonus system.
